        <h4 class="mb-3">What is a Regular Expression?</h4>
        <p>A regular expression is a formula that describes a regular language using symbols and operators. It is a way to write patterns for matching strings.</p>

        <h4 class="mt-4">Basic Regular Expression Syntax</h4>
        <ul>
            <li><b>&epsilon;</b>: Represents the language containing only the empty string.</li>
            <li><b>&empty;</b>: Represents the empty language (no strings).</li>
            <li><b>a</b>: Represents the language {a}.</li>
            <li><b>r + s</b>: Union (either r or s).</li>
            <li><b>rs</b>: Concatenation (r followed by s).</li>
            <li><b>r*</b>: Kleene star (zero or more repetitions of r).</li>
            <li><b>r+</b>: One or more repetitions of r.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="mt-4">Examples</h4>
        <div class="table-responsive bg-dark p-2 rounded">
            <table class="table table-bordered table-sm text-white">
                <thead class="table-light">
