                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td><code>a*</code></td><td>Any number of a's (including none)</td><td>&epsilon;, a, aa, aaa, ...</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>(a+b)*</code></td><td>All strings over {a, b}</td><td>&epsilon;, a, b, ab, ba, ...</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>ab*</code></td><td>'a' followed by any number of 'b's</td><td>a, ab, abb, abbb, ...</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>(ab)+</code></td><td>One or more repetitions of "ab"</td><td>ab, abab, ababab, ...</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>a(a+b)*b</code></td><td>Strings starting with 'a' and ending with 'b'</td><td>ab, aab, abb, aab, ...</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>

        <h4 class="mt-4">Regular Expressions and Languages: The Connection</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Every regular expression defines a regular language.</li>
            <li>Every regular language can be described by a regular expression.</li>
            <li>Regular expressions and finite automata are equivalent in power.</li>
        </ul>

